Implement `InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation()` | Sends direct HTTP POST via httpx | 0.5h |\n27: | 4.1.7 | Implement `InvokeRuntime._build_k8s_endpoint()` | Constructs endpoint from k8s_deployment info | 0.5h |\n28: | 4.1.8 | Add session header injection (`X-Agentcube-Session-Id`) | Header added if session_id in metadata | 0.5h |\n29: \n30: **Deliverable:** InvokeRuntime can invoke agents via both agentcube and k8s providers.\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## ST-4.2 — StatusRuntime Implementation\n35: \n36: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n37: |---|------|--------------|------|\n38: | 4.2.1 | Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` with `StatusRuntime` class | File exists with proper docstring and imports | 0.5h |\n39: | 4.2.2 | Implement `StatusRuntime.__init__()` with verbose, provider, logger, MetadataService | Logger level set; service instantiated | 0.5h |\n40: | 4.2.3 | Implement `StatusRuntime.get_status()` main entry point | Returns status dict with required keys | 0.5h |\n41: | 4.2.4 | Implement `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status()` | Queries Deployment/Service status via KubernetesProvider | 1h |\n42: | 4.2.5 | Implement `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` | Queries AgentRuntime CR via AgentCubeProvider | 1h |\n43: | 4.2.6 | Handle \"not_published\" status (no agent_id or k8s_deployment) | Returns proper status dict with message | 0.5h |\n44: | 4.2.7 | Handle \"error\" status (FileNotFoundError, API errors) | Returns proper error status dict | 0.5h |\n45: | 4.2.8 | Extract and return status fields: status, agent_name, agent_id, endpoint, provider, message | All fields present in response | 0.5h |\n46: \n47: **Deliverable:** StatusRuntime can check status via both agentcube and k8s providers.\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## ST-4.3 — AgentCubeProvider Extensions\n52: \n53: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n54: |---|------|--------------|------|\n55: | 4.3.1 | Add `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()` method | Returns CR dict or None; handles 404 | 0.5h |\n56: | 4.3.2 | Add CR_GROUP, CR_VERSION, CR_PLURAL class constants | Constants defined correctly | 0.25h |\n57: | 4.3.3 | Handle kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException in get_agent_runtime | 404 returns None; others raise | 0.5h |\n58: | 4.3.4 | Extract status fields from AgentRuntime CR | status, agentEndpoint extracted | 0.5h |\n59: \n60: **Deliverable:** AgentCubeProvider can retrieve AgentRuntime CR status.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## ST-4.4 — KubernetesProvider Status Method\n65: \n66: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n67: |---|------|--------------|------|\n68: | 4.4.1 | Verify `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` exists and works | Returns status dict with state, replicas, available_replicas | 0.5h |\n69: | 4.4.2 | Ensure status mapping logic: available == desired → \"ready\" | Logic correct | 0.25h |\n70: | 4.4.3 | Ensure status mapping: available < desired → \"pending\" | Logic correct | 0.25h |\n71: | 4.4.4 | Handle Deployment not found (404) → \"not_found\" | Returns proper status | 0.5h |\n72: \n73: **Deliverable:** KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status() works correctly.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## ST-4.5 — CLI Invoke Command\n78: \n79: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n80: |---|------|--------------|------|\n81: | 4.5.1 | Implement `invoke` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Command registered with Typer | 0.5h |\n82: | 4.5.2 | Add `--workspace` / `-f` option (default: \".\") | Option works; path resolved | 0.25h |\n83: | 4.5.3 | Add `--payload` option (default: \"{}\") | JSON string accepted | 0.25h |\n84: | 4.5.4 | Add `--header` option (multiple allowed) | Headers parsed as \"key:value\" | 0.5h |\n85: | 4.5.5 | Add `--provider` option (default: \"agentcube\") | Values: \"agentcube\", \"k8s\" | 0.25h |\n86: | 4.5.6 | Add `--verbose` option | Enables DEBUG logging | 0.25h |\n87: | 4.5.7 | Validate JSON payload format | JSONDecodeError handled with red message | 0.5h |\n88: | 4.5.8 | Validate header format (must contain \":\") | Error message on invalid format | 0.5h |\n89: | 4.5.9 | Parse headers into dict | Headers dict passed to runtime | 0.5h |\n90: | 4.5.10 | Create InvokeRuntime and call invoke() | Runtime instantiated correctly | 0.5h |\n91: | 4.5.11 | Display success message with Rich JSON output | console.print_json(data=result) | 0.5h |\n92: | 4.5.12 | Handle errors via `_handle_error()` | Exits with code 1 on error | 0.5h |\n93: | 4.5.13 | Add Rich Progress spinner during invocation | Progress shown during work | 0.5h |\n94: \n95: **Deliverable:** CLI invoke command works end-to-end with proper UI.\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## ST-4.6 — CLI Status Command\n100: \n101: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n102: |---|------|--------------|------|\n103: | 4.6.1 | Implement `status` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Command registered with Typer | 0.5h |\n104: | 4.6.2 | Add `--workspace` / `-f` option (default: \".\") | Option works; path resolved | 0.25h |\n105: | 4.6.3 | Add `--provider` option (default: \"agentcube\") | Values: \"agentcube\", \"k8s\" | 0.25h |\n106: | 4.6.4 | Add `--verbose` option | Enables DEBUG logging | 0.25h |\n107: | 4.6.5 | Create StatusRuntime and call get_status() | Runtime instantiated correctly | 0.5h |\n108: | 4.6.6 | Display status in Rich Table | Table with Property/Value columns | 0.5h |\n109: | 4.6.7 | Exit with code 1 if status is \"not_published\" or \"error\" | typer.Exit(1) on error status | 0.5h |\n110: | 4.6.8 | Handle errors via `_handle_error()` | Exits with code 1 on exception | 0.5h |\n111: \n112: **Deliverable:** CLI status command works end-to-end with proper UI.\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## ST-4.7 — Import and Wiring\n117: \n118: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n119: |---|------|--------------|------|\n120: | 4.7.1 | Import `InvokeRuntime` in `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Import at top of file | 0.25h |\n121: | 4.7.2 | Import `StatusRuntime` in `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Import at top of file | 0.25h |\n122: | 4.7.3 | Add `InvokeRuntime` to `