cube/cli/main.py` — invoke and status commands\n251: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` — Updated exports\n252: - [ ] `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` — get_agent_runtime method\n253: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_invoke_runtime.py` — InvokeRuntime unit tests\n254: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_status_runtime.py` — StatusRuntime unit tests\n255: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_cli_invoke.py` — CLI invoke tests\n256: - [ ] `tests/unit/test_cli_status.py` — CLI status tests\n257: - [ ] `tests/integration/test_invoke.py` — Invoke integration tests\n258: - [ ] `tests/integration/test_status.py` — Status integration tests\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## Verification Commands\n263: \n264: ```bash\n265: # Build/install verification\n266: pip install -e .\n267: \n268: # Import verification\n269: python -c \"from agentcube.runtime import InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime\"\n270: python -c \"from agentcube.cli.main import invoke, status\"\n271: \n272: # CLI entry point verification\n273: kubectl-agentcube --help\n274: kubectl-agentcube invoke --help\n275: kubectl-agentcube status --help\n276: \n277: # Unit test verification\n278: pytest tests/unit/test_invoke_runtime.py -v\n279: pytest tests/unit/test_status_runtime.py -v\n280: pytest tests/unit/test_cli_invoke.py -v\n281: pytest tests/unit/test_cli_status.py -v\n282: \n283: # Integration tests\n284: pytest tests/integration/test_invoke.py -v\n285: pytest tests/integration/test_status.py -v\n286: \n287: # Coverage report\n288: pytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n289: \n290: # Lint verification\n291: ruff check agentcube/\n292: mypy agentcube/\n293: ```\n294: \n295: ---\n296: \n297: ## Definition of Done\n298: \n299: - [ ] All 101 tasks complete\n300: - [ ] Package installs successfully (`pip install -e .`)\n301: - [ ] CLI commands work (`kubectl-agentcube invoke`, `kubectl-agentcube status`)\n302: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for each module)\n303: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n304: - [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n305: - [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n306: - [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ## Dependencies\n311: \n312: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` — CLI framework (already present)\n313: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation (already present)\n314: - `pyyaml>=6.0` — YAML parsing (already present)\n315: - `rich>=13.0.0` — Progress indicators and tables (already present)\n316: - `httpx>=0.24.0` — HTTP client for invocations (NEW)\n317: - `kubernetes>=28.0.0` — K8s client (already present)\n318: - `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework (already present)\n319: - `pytest-cov>=4.1.0` — Coverage reporting (already present)\n320: - `pytest-mock>=3.11.0` — Mocking utilities (already present)\n321: - `respx>=0.20.0` — httpx mocking for tests (NEW)\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## Design Notes\n326: \n327: - **Provider selection:** `--provider` accepts \"agentcube\" (AgentRuntime CR) or \"k8s\" (Deployment/Service)\n328: - **Payload format:** JSON string passed to `--payload`, validated before sending\n329: - **Header format:** `\"Key: Value\"` format, parsed into dict\n330: - **Session header:** `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` automatically added if session_id in metadata\n331: - **Status exit codes:** Exit code 1 for \"not_published\" or \"error\" statuses\n332: - **URL construction for agentcube:** `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n333: - **Error handling:** All errors use `_handle_error()` for consistent display\n334: - **Progress indication:** Rich Progress spinner during invoke operation\n335: - **Output formatting:** JSON for invoke, Rich Table for status\n\n(End of file - total 335 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-023  \n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n> **Language:** Python  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `invoke` and `status` CLI commands enable users to interact with deployed agents. The `invoke` command sends HTTP requests to agents with JSON payloads, while `status` retrieves the deployment state from either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — InvokeRuntime Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775895480987,"end":1775895481013}}}}
