{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895758034,"sessionID":"ses_28461db48ffeMJOvl72ZnwHnVc","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9fb544001f5mkHbi1NtUc5s","messageID":"msg_d7b9f7f1a001or6hgpbshepVxG","sessionID":"ses_28461db48ffeMJOvl72ZnwHnVc","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:17","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md","content":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-024  \n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n> **Language:** Python  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `DockerService` class provides a unified, high-level interface for Docker image operations within the AgentCube CLI. This service abstracts Docker SDK interactions for image building, tagging, pushing, and management, providing consistent error handling, logging, and result formatting across the CLI toolchain.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Core Service Implementation Verification\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.1.1 | Verify `DockerService` class exists in `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | File exists with proper docstring | 0.25h |\n| 4.1.2 | Verify `__init__(verbose=False)` initializes logger correctly | Logger level set based on verbose flag | 0.25h |\n| 4.1.3 | Verify `_get_client()` lazy-initializes Docker client with `from_env()` | Client created on first access, cached subsequently | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.4 | Verify `_get_client()` performs health check via `ping()` | Raises RuntimeError if Docker unavailable | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.5 | Verify `is_docker_available()` returns bool without raising | Returns True/False based on Docker daemon status | 0.25h |\n| 4.1.6 | Verify `_format_image_id()` helper truncates to 12 chars | \"sha256:abc123...\" → \"abc123\" (12 chars) | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Core service structure verified and working.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.2 — Image Building Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.2.1 | Verify `build_image()` validates Dockerfile exists | Raises FileNotFoundError with path | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.2 | Verify `build_image()` validates context path exists | Raises FileNotFoundError with path | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.3 | Verify `build_image()` computes relative Dockerfile path | Path relative to context calculated correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.4 | Verify `build_image()` passes build_args to Docker | buildargs parameter populated correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.5 | Verify `build_image()` tracks build duration | build_time field in result (seconds) | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.6 | Verify `build_image()` formats image size as \"XX.XXMB\" | Size converted from bytes to MB | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.7 | Verify `build_image()` extracts error from BuildError logs | RuntimeError includes specific error message | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.8 | Verify `build_image()` returns correct result dict | Contains all 6 required fields per spec | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Image building works with proper error handling and result formatting.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.3 — Image Tagging Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.3.1 | Verify `tag_image()` gets source image via client | `client.images.get(full_source)` called | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.2 | Verify `tag_image()` applies new tag via `image.tag()` | Tagging method invoked correctly | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.3 | Verify `tag_image()` returns result dict with source/target | Dict contains source, target, image_id | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.4 | Verify `tag_image()` handles DockerException | RuntimeError raised with context | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Image tagging works end-to-end.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.4 — Image Information & Listing\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.4.1 | Verify `get_image_info()` retrieves image via `client.images.get()` | Image fetched by full tag | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.2 | Verify `get_image_info()` formats size as \"XX.XXMB\" | Size field formatted correctly | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.3 | Verify `get_image_info()` returns all required fields | name, tag, id, size, created, labels | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.4 | Verify `get_image_info()` raises RuntimeError on missing image | Error message includes full tag | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.5 | Verify `list_images()` calls `client.images.list()` | List method invoked with name filter | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.6 | Verify `list_images()` handles images without tags | \"<none>:<none>\" default tag handling | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.7 | Verify `list_images()` returns list of image dicts | Each dict has name, tag, id, size, created | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.8 | Verify `list_images()` supports optional name filter | name parameter passed to client | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Image querying and listing works correctly.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.5 — Image Push Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.5.1 | Verify `push_image()` constructs full image name with registry | Registry URL prepended when provided | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.2 | Verify `push_image()` gets local image before push | `client.images.get(local_tag)` called | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.3 | Verify `push_image()` tags image for registry when needed | `image.tag()` called with registry prefix | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.4 | Verify `push_image()` logs in when credentials provided | `client.login()` called with username/password | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.5 | Verify `push_image()` streams push logs with decode=True | Stream=True and decode=True parameters | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.6 | Verify `push_image()` detects errors in push logs | RuntimeError raised on error in stream | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.7 | Verify `push_image()` returns result dict with pushed=True | Dict contains image_name, tag, registry, pushed | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.8 | Verify `push_image()` handles DockerException | RuntimeError raised with error message | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Image push works with authentication and error detection.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.6 — Credential Extraction\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.6.1 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` parses user:pass@host format | Credentials extracted from URL | 0.25h |\n| 4.6.2 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` URL-decodes credentials | Special characters like @, # decoded | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.3 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` reconstructs clean URL | Credentials removed from returned URL | 0.25h |\n| 4.6.4 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` handles URLs without credentials | Returns original URL, None for user/pass | 0.25h |\n| 4.6.5 | Verify `extract_credentials_from_url()` preserves port if present | Port included in clean URL | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Credential extraction works for embedded auth URLs.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.7 — Service Export Verification\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.7.1 | Verify `DockerService` exported from `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Import works: `from agentcube.services import DockerService` | 0.25h |\n| 4.7.2 | Verify `DockerService` in `__all__` list | Listed in __all__ exports | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Service is properly importable from package.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.8 — Unit Tests — DockerService Core\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.8.1 | Write `TestDockerServiceInit` — initialization with verbose=True | Logger set to DEBUG level | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.2 | Write `TestDockerServiceInit` — initialization with verbose=False | Logger set to INFO level | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.3 | Write `TestDockerServiceClient` — _get_client creates client once | Client cached, from_env called once | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.4 | Write `TestDockerServiceClient` — _get_client raises on DockerException | RuntimeError raised with message | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.5 | Write `TestDockerServiceClient` — _get_client calls ping() | Health check performed | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.6 | Write `TestDockerServiceAvailability` — is_docke